\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 67.     CAPPARACEAE}
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  Edit. V.H. Heywood.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Herbs, shrubs or trees. Leaves simple, or ternate to palmate, alternate, stipulate or not; stipules sometimes spinose. Flowers solitary or in racemes, actinomorphic or more usually zygomorphic, hermaphrodite. Sepals 4. Petals 4. Stamens 6 to many. Ovary 1, superior, on a gynophore; carpels 2. Fruit a 2-valved, unilocular capsule, or a berry.
\par

