\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 3.           Polanisia}          Rafin.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By J.R. Akeroyd.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Like {\i Cleome} but stamens 12-16; capsule linear to oblong, sessile or on a very short gynophore.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. P. trachysperma} Torrey & A. Gray,{\i  Fl. N. Amer.}{\b  1}: 669 (1840) ({\i P. dodecandra }(L.) DC. var.{\i  trachysperma} (Torrey & Gray) Iltis). Stems 20-50 cm, erect. Leaves petiolate, ternate; leaflets 3-7 cm, elliptical or oblong, obtuse, entire. Petals 8-12 mm, yellowish-white, bifid, the blade usually shorter than the claw. Stamens 12-16; filaments unequal, up to 20 mm, long-exserted, purple. Fruit 3-7 cm, erect, linear to oblong. Seeds c. 2 mm, areolate.{\i  Naturalized in N.W. & N.C. Italy.} [It.] ({\i North America}.)
